00:27.760 --> 00:31.840
The Gospel of Mark Chapter 15

00:32.360 --> 00:40.300
And straightway in the morning the chief priest held a consultation with the elders and the scribes and the whole council,

00:40.860 --> 00:46.620
and bound Jesus, and carried him away, and delivered him to Pilate.

00:46.620 --> 00:51.180
And Pilate asked him, Art thou the king of the Jews?

00:51.300 --> 00:54.940
And he answering said unto them, Thou sayest it.

00:55.900 --> 01:02.140
And the chief priest accused him of many things, but he answered nothing.

01:02.640 --> 01:06.500
And Pilate asked him again, saying, Answers thou nothing?

01:07.160 --> 01:10.460
Behold, how many things they witness against thee!

01:10.960 --> 01:15.740
But Jesus yet answered nothing, so that Pilate marveled.

01:15.740 --> 01:22.840
Now at that feast he released unto them one prisoner, whom soever they desired.

01:23.380 --> 01:33.680
And there was one named Barabbas, which lay bound with them, that had made insurrection against him,

01:33.860 --> 01:37.380
who had committed murder in the insurrection.

01:37.380 --> 01:45.920
And the multitude, crying aloud, began to desire him to do as he had ever done unto them.

01:46.220 --> 01:54.140
But Pilate answered them, saying, Will ye that I release unto you the king of the Jews?

01:54.660 --> 01:59.180
For he knew that the chief priest had delivered him for envy.

01:59.660 --> 02:06.680
But the chief priest moved the people, that he should rather release Barabbas unto them.

02:07.320 --> 02:19.080
And Pilate answered and said again unto them, What will ye then that I shall do unto him whom ye call the king of the Jews?

02:19.380 --> 02:22.520
And they cried out again, Crucify him.

02:22.900 --> 02:26.840
Then Pilate said unto them, Why, what evil hath he done?

02:27.140 --> 02:31.420
And they cried out the more exceedingly, Crucify him.

02:31.420 --> 02:36.960
And so Pilate, willing to content the people, released Barabbas unto them,

02:37.340 --> 02:42.260
and delivered Jesus when he had scourged him to be crucified.

02:42.900 --> 02:49.740
And the soldiers led him away into the hall, called Praetorium.

02:50.340 --> 02:58.660
And they called together the whole band, and they clothed him with purple, and plaited a crown of thorns,

02:58.660 --> 03:05.420
and put it upon his head, and began to salute him, Hail, King of the Jews!

03:05.800 --> 03:15.380
And they smote him on the head with a reed, and did spit upon him, and bowing their knees worshiped him.

03:15.660 --> 03:23.920
And when they had mocked him, they took off the purple from him, and put his own clothes on him,

03:23.920 --> 03:27.420
and led him out to crucify him.

03:27.620 --> 03:35.640
And they compel one, Simon, a Serenian, who passed by, coming out of the country,

03:36.140 --> 03:41.200
the father of Alexander and Rufus, to bear his cross.

03:41.500 --> 03:49.740
And they bring him unto the place, Golgotha, which is being interpreted the place of a skull.

03:50.300 --> 03:58.060
And they gave him to drink wine, mingled with myrrh, but he received it not.

03:58.380 --> 04:05.040
And when they had crucified him, they parted his garments, casting lots upon them,

04:05.140 --> 04:07.580
what every man should take.

04:07.940 --> 04:11.840
And it was the third hour, and they crucified him.

04:11.840 --> 04:20.260
And the superscription of his accusation was written over the King of the Jews.

04:20.900 --> 04:27.660
And with him they crucified two thieves, the one on his right hand, and the other on his left.

04:28.220 --> 04:34.600
And the scripture was fulfilled which saith, and he was numbered with the transgressors.

04:34.600 --> 04:40.540
And they that passed by railed on him, wagging their heads and saying,

04:41.140 --> 04:45.180
Ah, thou that destroyest the temple and buildest it in three days,

04:45.740 --> 04:48.860
save thyself and come down from the cross.

04:49.540 --> 04:55.880
Likewise also the chief priests, mocking, said among themselves with the scribes,

04:56.160 --> 05:00.080
he saved others, himself he cannot save.

05:00.720 --> 05:08.680
Let Christ the King of Israel descend now from the cross that we may see and believe.

05:09.300 --> 05:14.140
And they that were crucified with him reviled him.

05:14.460 --> 05:23.060
And when the sixth hour was come, there was darkness over the whole land until the ninth hour.

05:23.660 --> 05:28.480
And at the ninth hour Jesus cried with a loud voice saying,

05:29.360 --> 05:34.580
Eloi, Eloi lama sabachthani, which is being interpreted,

05:35.120 --> 05:40.380
My God, my God, why hast thou forsaken me?

05:40.940 --> 05:47.200
And some of them that stood by when they heard it said, Behold, he calleth Elias.

05:47.780 --> 05:55.580
And one ran and filled a sponge full of vinegar and put it on a reed and gave him to drink,

05:55.580 --> 06:01.100
saying, Let alone, let us see whether Elias will come to take him down.

06:01.460 --> 06:06.280
And Jesus cried with a loud voice and gave up the ghost.

06:07.280 --> 06:11.740
And the veil of the temple was rent entwined from the top to the bottom.

06:12.060 --> 06:19.780
And when the centurion which stood over against him saw that he so cried out and gave up the ghost,

06:20.340 --> 06:24.820
he said, Truly, this man was the Son of God.

06:25.330 --> 06:33.680
There were also women looking on afar off, among whom was Mary Magdalene and Mary,

06:33.820 --> 06:41.860
the mother of James, the less, and Jose's and Salome, who also when he was in Galilee followed

06:41.860 --> 06:49.740
him and ministered unto him, and many other women which came up with him unto Jerusalem.

06:49.740 --> 06:58.120
And now, when the even was come, because it was the preparation that is the day before the Sabbath,

06:59.120 --> 07:06.760
Joseph of Aramaothea, an honorable counselor, which also waited for the kingdom of God,

07:06.820 --> 07:13.340
came and went in boldly unto Pilate and craved the body of Jesus.

07:14.120 --> 07:20.640
And Pilate marveled if he were already dead, and calling unto him the centurion,

07:21.040 --> 07:24.620
he asked him whether he had been any while dead.

07:24.980 --> 07:30.480
And when he knew it of the centurion, he gave the body to Joseph.

07:31.440 --> 07:41.820
And he bought fine linen and took him down and wrapped him in the linen, and laid him in a

07:41.820 --> 07:46.340
rock, and rolled a stone on to the door of the sepulcher.

07:47.540 --> 07:53.160
And Mary Magdalene and Mary, the mother of Joseus, beheld where he was laid.

07:54.920 --> 08:02.740
And when the Sabbath was passed, Mary Magdalene and Mary, the mother of James and Salome,

08:03.020 --> 08:08.080
had bought sweet spices that they might come and anoint him.

08:08.080 --> 08:12.760
And very early in the morning, the first day of the week, they came

08:13.280 --> 08:18.860
unto the sepulcher at the rising of the sun. And they said among themselves,

08:19.340 --> 08:23.920
Who shall roll away the stone from the door of the sepulcher?

08:24.520 --> 08:30.980
And when they looked, they saw that the stone was rolled away, for it was very great.

08:30.980 --> 08:38.060
And entering into the sepulcher, they saw a young man sitting on the right side,

08:38.200 --> 08:42.820
clothed in a long white garment, and they were affrighted.

08:43.980 --> 08:51.320
And he saith unto them, Be not affrighted, ye seek Jesus of Nazareth, which was crucified.

08:51.700 --> 08:58.140
He is risen, he is not here. Behold the place where they laid him.

08:58.940 --> 09:06.680
But go your way, tell his disciples and Peter, that he goeth before you into Galilee.

09:07.120 --> 09:11.440
There shall ye see him, as he said unto you.

09:11.920 --> 09:18.000
And they went out quickly and fled from the sepulcher, for they trembled and were amazed.

09:18.280 --> 09:22.660
Neither said they anything to any man, for they were afraid.

09:23.180 --> 09:26.960
Now when Jesus was risen early the first day of the week,

09:27.360 --> 09:33.060
he appeared first to Mary Magdalene, out of whom he had cast seven devils.

09:33.900 --> 09:39.920
And she went and told them that had been with him as they mourned and wept.

09:40.500 --> 09:48.620
And they, when they heard that he was alive and had been seen of her, believed not.

09:49.420 --> 09:57.320
After that he appeared in another form unto two of them, as they walked and went into the country.

09:57.840 --> 10:03.180
And they went and told it unto the residue, neither believed they them.

10:03.880 --> 10:11.880
Afterward he appeared unto the eleven as they sat at meet, and upbraided them with their unbelief

10:11.880 --> 10:18.520
and heartness of heart, because they believed not them which had seen him after he was risen.

10:18.620 --> 10:26.360
And he said unto them, Go ye into all the world and preach the gospel to every creature.

10:27.040 --> 10:31.620
He that believeth and is baptized shall be saved.

10:32.140 --> 10:35.160
But he that believeth not shall be damned.

10:35.800 --> 10:39.480
And these signs shall follow them that believe.

10:40.300 --> 10:45.920
In my name shall they cast out devils. They shall speak with new tongues.

10:45.920 --> 10:52.800
They shall take up serpents, and if they drink any deadly thing, it shall not hurt them.

10:53.020 --> 10:57.560
They shall lay hands on the sick, and they shall recover.

10:58.480 --> 11:06.320
So then, after the Lord had spoken unto them, he was received up into heaven and sat

11:06.320 --> 11:13.160
on the right hand of God. And they went forth and preached everywhere the Lord,

11:13.160 --> 11:20.880
working with them and confirming the word with signs following. Amen.

11:21.980 --> 11:31.640
End of chapters 15 and 16. End of the Gospel of Mark, King James Version.

11:31.640 --> 11:35.820
Recording by Simon Wainwright.

